  "local_port": 40210,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some best resume?",
  "response": "Creating an effective resume is crucial for making a strong first impression on potential employers. Here are some best practices and formats that can enhance the quality of your resume:\n\n### Best Practices for Resume Writing\n\n1. **Tailor Your Resume**: Customize your resume for each job application by highlighting relevant experience, skills, and accomplishments that match the job description.\n\n2. **Use Clear Formatting**: Choose a clean and professional layout. Use headings, bullet points, and consistent font styles to improve readability.\n\n3. **Start with a Strong Summary or Objective**: A well-crafted summary or objective statement can quickly convey your qualifications and career goals.\n\n4. **Highlight Accomplishments**: Focus on achievements rather than just duties. Use metrics and specific examples to demonstrate your impact (e.g., \u201cIncreased sales by 30% in Q2\u201d).\n\n5. **Use Action Verbs**: Start bullet points with strong action verbs (e.g., developed, managed, led, optimized) to convey proactivity.\n\n6. **Keep it Concise**: Aim for one page if you have less than 10 years of experience. For more experienced professionals, two pages can be appropriate.\n\n7. **Include Keywords**: Incorporate industry-specific keywords and phrases that are likely used in the job posting to pass Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS).\n\n8. **Education and Certifications**: List your education and relevant certifications clearly, including any honors or relevant coursework.\n\n9. **Professional Development**: Mention workshops, courses, or trainings that demonstrate your continued professional growth.\n\n10. **Contact Information**: Include your full name, phone number, email address, and LinkedIn profile if applicable. Make sure your email address is professional.\n\n### Popular Resume Formats\n\n1. **Chronological Resume**: Lists work experience in reverse chronological order. This format is best for those with a strong and continuous work history.\n\n   **Example Structure**:\n   ```\n   [Your Name]\n   [Phone Number] | [Email Address] | [LinkedIn Profile] \n\n   Summary:\n   [1-2 sentences about your professional background]\n\n   Experience:\n   Job Title | Company Name | Location | Dates\n   - Responsibility/achievement\n   - Responsibility/achievement\n\n   Education:\n   Degree | Major | School Name | Graduation Date\n   ```\n\n2. **Functional Resume**: Focuses on skills and experiences rather than chronological work history. Ideal for those with gaps in employment or changing careers.\n\n   **Example Structure**:\n   ```\n   [Your Name]\n   [Contact Info] \n\n   Skills:\n   - Skill/competency 1\n   - Skill/competency 2\n\n   Experience:\n   Role 1 | Relevant Skills/Projects\n   Role 2 | Relevant Skills/Projects\n\n   Education:\n   [Your Education]\n   ```\n\n3. **Combination Resume**: Merges elements from both chronological and functional resumes, allowing for a detailed view of skills and relevant work history.\n\n   **Example Structure**:\n   ```\n   [Your Name]\n   [Contact Info] \n\n   Summary:\n   [Short summary]\n\n   Skills:\n   - Skill 1\n   - Skill 2\n\n   Experience:\n   Job Title | Company Name | Location | Dates\n   - Responsibility/Achievement\n   Job Title | Company Name | Location | Dates\n   - Responsibility/Achievement\n\n   Education:\n   [Your Education]\n   ```\n\n4. **Creative Resume**: Suitable for fields like design or media, creative resumes allow for more artistic elements and unique layouts. However, they should still maintain professionalism and readability.\n\n### Additional Tips\n\n- **Proofread**: Always check for spelling and grammatical errors.\n- **Consistency**: Ensure that font sizes, styles, and spacing are consistent throughout the resume.\n- **Include a Portfolio**: If relevant, provide a link to a portfolio showcasing your work.\n\nUltimately, the best resume is one that accurately represents your skills and experiences while being tailored to the specific job you're applying for.",
